2714. FROM CHRISTOPHER EsCHENFELDER.

Leipzig MS. Boppard. ΕΕ. 177. 2 September 1532.

[An original letter, autograph throughout : on the blank half of the verso are some hasty scribblings by Erasmus. For Eschenfelden See Ep. 879 introd]

S. P. D. Inmortales ago tibi gracias et habebo dum vixero, Erasme doctissime idemque animo meo charissime, qui inter tot et tanta negocia me tuis iucundissimis literis dignatus sis honor- are. Vellem tibi constaret,
